Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Located 100m from the intersection of the Wakehurst Parkway and Aquatic Drive, on the western side of Tilley Lane in the Frenchs Forest Business Park, 500m from the Northern Beaches Hospital.

Features:
• Modern office, refurbished with new carpet and LED lighting
• Kitchenette and WC facilities on ground and office level
• High Clearance warehouse 8-12m clearance
• Cabled, CCTV, Security Bollard, Access Control, 100/100 TPG Fibre
• Bonus optional 68sqm warehouse mezzanine
• Available now for immediate occupation
- Long lease terms available 
- Rare freestanding building with own yard/hardstand in front

For further details please contact CBRE: Ben Byford- Exclusive Leasing Agent.

CBRE, as the exclusive sales agent, is pleased to present Building 10, Frenchs Forest Business Park, Frenchs Forest. This modern three storey commercial freehold building was completed in 2003, with a building area of 1,545sqm*. The property is 100% leased to multinational watch manufacturer - Citizen Australia. Building 10, Frenchs Forest Business Park, Frenchs Forest holds a prime location just moments from the new Northern Beaches Hospital which opened to the public at the end of 2018.

Building 10,  Frenchs Forest Business Park, Frenchs Forest capitalises on the following key attributes:

- 100% leased to multinational watch manufacturer – Citizen Australia. Having operated from the building since its completion in 2003, Citizen Australia is a long-term tenant with international acclaim.   
- Building area of 1,545sqm* plus 29 car spaces 
- Net income of $572,073 per annum*
- Strategic location set for growth for the next 20 years driven by the new hospital and future Frenchs Forest Town Centre
- Significant rental reversion opportunity 


Building 10,  Frenchs Forest Business Park, Frenchs Forest  will be sold via expressions of interest closing on Wednesday, 28 August 2019 at 4.00pm.



For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

*Approximate

Note: All financial figures have been provided by the Vendor. Purchasers are advised to conduct their own independent due diligence.

The site of 8,197sqm* is rectangular in configuration with a 3 level onsite building leased to 3M Australia until 10 January 2017, plus an extensive unimproved grassed area at the rear of the property. The onsite building comprises 2,320sqm*. There is also a basement car park not included in this measurement. The broad area for this is estimated in the order of 650sqm* subject to survey.

The property is well placed to enjoy future value growth given the proximity to the new hospital; enhanced accessibility arising from the road infrastructure improvements at the junction of Warringah Road and Wakehurst Parkway; the anticipated Structure Plan and associated LEP relaxation, along with the broad growth anticipated in the next 5-10 years across the Northern Beaches.

*Approx.

For sale via Expressions of Interest closing Thursday 22 September 2016.
